commit.message:
Flatten single-item submenus (#132)

Nautilus 43+ uses Gtk4 context menus, where submenus have to be
clicked on and entered instead of opening on hover. This makes
accessing submenus containing only a single item needlessly tedious.

So, we detect when the Dropbox submenu will only contain a single
selection, and promote it up to the top level instead of burying
it within an unnecessary submenu layer.

commit.message:
Update the build and packaging script for Fedora 37. (#109)

Fedora 37 includes GNOME 43, which is not backwards compatible with packages built against older versions. We used to build new Fedora versions on Ubuntu, but they removed support for building RPM packages in 20.04. By updating the build script to run on Fedora, this allows us to release coreyberla's fix, resolving #108 and #101.

Co-authored-by: Geoffry Song <goffrie@dropbox.com>
